Silverback Asset Management - Home
















Client Login
Username
Password





















Silverback Asset Management was founded in 2002 by Elliot Bossen, who has over 35 years of investment experience. Mr. Bossen leads a talented investment team, guides the firm's investments, and oversees an experienced business team that leverages a network of strong partnerships within the financial industry.  






Silverback is an alternative investment firm that specializes in convertible securities as it manages arbitrage and relative value strategies for institutional investors. Silverback's expertise spans credit, equity, and volatility markets. Silverback, an SEC registered investment advisor, is based in Chapel Hill, North Carolina.






We pride ourselves on developing creative solutions to meet the needs of institutional investors. If you work for or consult a pension fund, endowment, insurance company, government agency, foundation, sovereign wealth fund, fund of funds, or family office, please contact Silverback to discuss your investment needs.






The content on this website is for information purposes only and does not constitute an offer to sell or the solicitation of an offer to buy either shares or interests in any funds or partnerships, nor should such content be construed as a recommendation of any investment services referenced herein.  An offer or solicitation will be made only by means of a confidential information memorandum and subscription agreement to a particular fund or partnership, only in jurisdictions in which such an offer, solicitation or sale would be lawful, and only to accredited investors who meet the suitability and qualification requirements for such fund or partnership.  Investments in hedge funds are speculative, have limited liquidity, and involve a high degree of risk.  There can be no assurance that any hedge fund’s investment objectives will be achieved and investment results may vary substantially over time.  Investments in hedge funds are not intended to be a complete investment program for any investor.  Investments in hedge funds are intended for sophisticated investors who are able to understand the risks involved and can bear the economic risk of loss in their investments.  





