Company Description


Silverback Asset Management manages funds that that employ a convertible arbitrage strategy and funds that invest primarily in “litigation finance” companies. The firm's convertible arbitrage strategy seeks to capture returns from investments in credit, equity, volatility, and event-driven opportunities; but also may make investments in related strategies, including capital structure arbitrage and equity volatility arbitrage. Silverback actively manages exposures to equity, credit, volatility and interest rates, and may mitigate these risks via hedges where appropriate. To implement hedges and hedging strategies,the the firm engages in short selling and options trading and may utilize derivatives (e.g. credit default swaps), interest rate swaps, and futures and forward contracts. Silverback serves as investment manager to two private funds formed as partnerships which invest primarily in an emerging industry known as “litigation finance.\"\" The strategy focuses on privately-negotiated investments in loans and private securities (specifically, asset-based high yield debt and equity); investments involving non-traditional and emerging asset financing techniques implemented through the combination of various privately negotiated investment agreements and vehicles; and investments in a non-diversified portfolio of illiquid and hard-to-value assets. The funds may employ the use of leverage.




